Update to v0.9.22

 - Actually follow spec on AppID parsing. Fixes #27
 - Remove infobars in favor of notifications
 - Enforce tab-in-foreground policy to tie user action to origin
 - Store eTLD list in JavaScript to avoid an internal xhr
 - Comment and code-style cleanup for updated Closure
 - Refactoring and minor fixes

Update to v0.9.6

 - Fix bug where the extension would not respond under certain
   circumstances.
 - Fix bug in user approval UI
 - Send a valid V1 enroll request to blink unregistered V1 gnubbies

Update to v0.9.3

 - Require explicit user approval on registration
 - Embed eTLD list instead of fetching remotel
 - Support compressed requests (single appId and challenge)
 - Do not reveal to webpage if that a device is enrolled without explicit user action
 - Smaller bugfixes

Bugfix 0.8.68.2

 - Infobars are badly broken on mac in Chrome, so we must bypass them.

Bugfix 0.8.68.1

 - Only trigger infobar if the API is actually available
 - Log strings instead of objects, better for chrome://extensions

Update to 0.8.68

 - Show an infobar on enroll to get explicit user's consent.
 - Smaller fixes and refactoring

Update to 0.8.64

 - Better error reporting
 - Enumerate HID devices by usagePage 0xF1D0 on Chrome 39+
 - Refactoring

Update to 0.8.63
 - Correctly check for chrome.usb.open failure
 - Catch errors in sendResponse
 - Handle CMD_INIT as CMD_SYNC
 - Avoid race by special handling of non-HID devices
 - Smaller bug fixes/refactoring

 * Implements the proposed eTLD+1 check on appIds
 * Some refactoring/cleanups

commit_list.message:
Clarify the U2F Attestation format to have a single certificate

The [U2F Raw Message Format](https://fidoalliance.org/specs/fido-u2f-v1.2-ps-20170411/fido-u2f-raw-message-formats-v1.2-ps-20170411.html#h3_registration-response-message-success) only allows for a single attestation certificate in U2F responses.

This PR reflects this in the U2F Attestation Format to reduce the chance of misunderstanding when implementing the server verification.
